# Trivy ignore list — documented triage.
#
# RULES:
#   1. Every entry has an owner, a reason, and an expected resolution date.
#   2. Reviewed monthly. If a CVE is still here next review, escalate.
#   3. App-level CVEs do NOT belong here; only OS/base-image CVEs where the
#      fix is outside our repo's direct control go here.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# libssl3 / OpenSSL on Debian 12 base of gcr.io/distroless/nodejs20-debian12.
# Status: fixed upstream in 3.0.19-1~deb12u2. Distroless rolling tag
# (:nonroot) has not yet picked up the rebuilt openssl as of this commit.
# Mitigation: app does no TLS termination of its own (ingress handles it)
# and does not parse untrusted X.509 certificates, so practical exposure
# to these specific CVEs in our service is limited.
# Owner: AdrDmy
# Tracked: https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless/issues
# Expected resolution: next distroless rebuild (typically <14 days).
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-31789
CVE-2026-28387
CVE-2026-28388
CVE-2026-28389
